  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Elimination of water borne diseases in Nyakach</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IWHA&apos;s goal: Eliminate water-borne diseases such as diarrhea, typhoid and cholera in 14,400 families, 69,000 people in Lower Nyakach, Kenya . Combining easily understood, effective and low cost community-based water testing, education, and chlorine treatment enables families to kill disease-causing germs in unsafe drinking water from streams, ponds, and wells. This project to prevent diseases and save lives can be replicated in millions of villages plagued by water-borne diseases worldwide.</narrative>
  </description>
